            <h2>Drain inspection FAQs</h2>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-list">
            <div class="faq-item"><button type="button" aria-expanded="false">How long does a drain inspection take?</button><div><p>Most residential inspections take 30 minutes to one hour, depending on the size and complexity of your drain system and how many lines need to be inspected.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item"><button type="button" aria-expanded="false">Is camera inspection safe for my pipes?</button><div><p>Yes. Our cameras are designed to be flexible and gentle. They will not damage your pipes. The equipment navigates bends and joints without scratching or stressing the pipe walls.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item"><button type="button" aria-expanded="false">What is sewer smoke testing?</button><div><p>Sewer smoke testing uses harmless artificial smoke pumped into the drain system to find leaks, cracks, and breaks. The smoke exits at problem points, making them easy to identify above ground. It is especially useful for tracking down persistent odors.</p></div></div>
